You are trying to read `r.Body` twice, first in `commonMiddleware` with `ioutil.ReadAll(r.Body)` and then in `handleNumber` with `r.ParseForm()`. You can't do that because `r.Body` is an `io.Reader` and you can't read it two times. 

To fix this issue, you can parse the form data in the middleware using `r.ParseForm()` and then use the parsed form data. In the middleware, you can use `r.PostForm.Encode()` to log the form data, and in the handler, you can use `r.FormValue()` or `r.Form.Get()` to extract the form data.

Here's an updated version of your code:

```go
func commonMiddleware(next http.Handler) http.Handler {
  return http.HandlerFunc(func(w http.ResponseWriter, r *http.Request) {
    w.Header().Add("Content-Type", "application/json")
    err := r.ParseForm() // parse in middleware, data will be contained in r.PostForm
    if err != nil {
      log.Fatalf("Failed to decode postFormByteSlice: %v", err)
    }
    rl := rLog{Method: r.Method, URI: r.RequestURI, FormParam: r.PostForm.Encode()} // url.Values.Encode() stringifies form data
    log.Printf("%+v", rl)
    next.ServeHTTP(w, r)
  })
}

func main() {
  port := ":3000"
  var router = mux.NewRouter()
  router.Use(commonMiddleware)
  router.HandleFunc("/m/{msg}", handleMessage).Methods("GET")
  router.HandleFunc("/n/", handleNumber).Methods("POST")
}

func handleNumber(w http.ResponseWriter, r *http.Request) {
  log.Println(r.PostForm.Get("name")) // or just r.Form.Get("name") or r.FormValue("name")
  response := map[string]string{"name": "1"} // dummy response
  json.NewEncoder(w).Encode(response)
}
```

In the updated code, `r.ParseForm()` is called in the middleware to parse the form data, which will be contained in `r.PostForm`. The `FormParam` field in the `rLog` struct is set to `r.PostForm.Encode()` to log the form data as a string. In the `handleNumber` handler, you can use `r.PostForm.Get("name")` to access the value of the `name` field in the form data.

