To optimize the tracking and analysis, you can use a few techniques:
1. Store the session data in a local database or file instead of in memory. This can improve performance and allow you to store larger amounts of data.
2. Use background processing to track sessions even when the app is not in use. This can ensure that all sessions are captured and prevent data loss.
3. Use analytics tools to analyze the data and identify trends or patterns. This can help you make data-driven decisions about how to improve your app or user experience.
Here's an example of how you might implement the session tracking and analysis in Swift:
```swift
// Define the session data structure
struct SkiSession {
    let date: Date
    let startTime: Date
    let endTime: Date
    var duration: TimeInterval {
        return endTime.timeIntervalSince(startTime)
    }
}
// Store the sessions in an array
var sessions: [SkiSession] = []
// Add a new session to the array
func addSession(date: Date, startTime: Date, endTime: Date) {
    let session = SkiSession(date: date, startTime: startTime, endTime: endTime)
    sessions.append(session)
}
// Calculate the total duration of all sessions
func totalDuration() -> TimeInterval {
